  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Laparoscopic inguinal hernia repair techniques has been compared with the open techniques in
      several studies. However, no one studied about the different uses of the same type of mesh on
      the same surgical technique, and effects of this different use on testicular volume and blood
      flow. The objective of this study is to investigate the effects at 6 months of the divided
      and non divided mesh in laparoscopic totally extraperitoneal hernia repair technique on
      testicular volume and blood flow by use of Doppler Ultrasonography
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
